org.apache.poi.xssf.model
Class CalculationChain

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.poi.POIXMLDocumentPart
      org.apache.poi.xssf.model.CalculationChain

public class CalculationChain
extends POIXMLDocumentPart

The cells in a workbook can be calculated in different orders depending on various optimizations and dependencies. The calculation chain object specifies the order in which the cells in a workbook were last calculated.

Author:
Yegor Kozlov

commit

protected void commit()
               throws java.io.IOException
Description copied from class: POIXMLDocumentPart
Save the content in the underlying package part. Default implementation is empty meaning that the package part is left unmodified. Sub-classes should override and add logic to marshal the "model" into Ooxml4J. For example, the code saving a generic XML entry may look as follows: 

 protected void commit() throws IOException {
   PackagePart part = getPackagePart();
   OutputStream out = part.getOutputStream();
   XmlObject bean = getXmlBean(); //the "model" which holds changes in memory
   bean.save(out, DEFAULT_XML_OPTIONS);
   out.close();
 }
